# SmartPerfetto Cursor Rules

Use the repository root `AGENTS.md` as the canonical project guide. Before code
edits, read `AGENTS.md` and the relevant detailed rule file under
`.claude/rules/`.

Essential invariants:

- Node.js 24 LTS, TypeScript strict mode, Express backend, forked Perfetto UI.
- Do not hardcode prompt content in TypeScript; use `backend/strategies/` and
  `backend/skills/`.
- Default user startup is `./start.sh`; use `./scripts/start-dev.sh` only for
  Perfetto UI plugin development.
- After AI Assistant plugin UI changes, verify in the browser and run
  `./scripts/update-frontend.sh` before committing.
- Portable releases must follow the versioned, clean-release workflow in
  `AGENTS.md` and `.claude/rules/git.md`: commit the version bump first, build
  the Windows/macOS/Linux assets, verify manifests, and do not publish public
  releases with `--allow-dirty`.
- Run the verification tier from `AGENTS.md`; before PR, run `npm run verify:pr`.
